BFN 

  [Text] Today, Azerbaijani President Geydar Aliyev received 
a delegation led by the Iranian Petroleum Minister Gholam Reza 
Aqazadeh-Kho'i. 
  [Begin Nermine Elikhanbeyli recording] In conveying the 
greetings of the Iranian Government, Mr. Gholam Reza 
Aqazadeh-Kho'i said during his meeting with the Azerbaijani 
president that he considers the development of beneficial 
cooperation between the two neighboring states as imperative. 
According to the minister, Iran is taking practical steps in 
this direction. The memorandum on laying a gas pipeline to 
Nakhichevan has already been ratified by Iran. 
  In noting that he gives great importance to 
Iranian-Azerbaijani ties, President Geydar Aliyev stated that 
our republic is ready to cooperate with the neighboring state in 
every field. Therefore, it complies with our state policy to 
regard Iran as a system with which to cooperate. 
  President noted that he will be visiting Iran in the near 
future, and hopes his visit will produce practical results. 
  Fuat Guliyev, first deputy prime minister; State Adviser 
Vafa 
Gulizade; Natiq Aliyev, the president of the State Oil Company; 
'Ali Akbar Nahavandian, Iranian ambassador to Azerbaijan; 'Ali 
Abdul Alizadeh, governor of East Azerbaijan; and other officials 
took part in the meeting. 
  Rasul Guliyev, the head of the Azerbaijani Parliament, also 
met with the delegation today and said that Azerbaijan, which 
wishes to emerge on the international scene, is pinning great 
hopes on its economic ties in the oil sector. Therefore, he 
noted, priority will continue to be given to intensive 
cooperation with the neighboring states. 
  Afiaddin Dzhalilov, deputy chairman of the republic's 
Supreme 
Soviet, the Iranian Ambassador to Azerbaijan 'Ali Akbar 
Nahavandian, and other officials were present at the meeting. 
[end recording] 

